{
  "texts": [
    "BTM assumes that a pair of words can reveal topics much better than a single word occurrence.",
    "However, BTM uses Gibbs sampling to infer topics",
    "Evaluation Metrics Score Coherence Score (Cv): 0.41729641207699614 Coherence Score (UMass) -3.134660752974013 Perplexity -6.702164919787796 Table 7 Evaluation of LDA topics 1 3 and has been criticised to be very time consuming and thus, FastBTM (He et al. 2017) was developed.",
    "Notable variants of BTM proposed are User-iBTM (Li and Xu 2016), and adaptive online bi-term topic modelling (Hadi and Fard 2020) to model the dynamics of topics over time.",
    "However, these techniques have been criticised to bring in little additional word co-occurrence information and therefore still face data sparsity problem."
  ]
}